  "text": "During clustering phase each node generates a random number between 0 and 1. If the number is below the predefined threshold value T (n), then that node is elected to be the candidate for the selection of a cluster head. Let the number of CHs getting elected in each round be C i (i = 1, 2, ..., N ) . Equation [CITATION_1] ensures that the responsibility of being a cluster head gets rotated among all the nodes and the nodes with higher residual energy than other nodes are elected to be the cluster heads. But to improve the network performance other factors can be incorporated to influence the decision of the final CH selection. Thus, the nodes need to be embedded with a fuzzy system to meet the said requirement.",
